A MUST try. Bongiorno’s is my favorite Italian restaurant (or restaurant in general for that matter) in Chicago. Very reasonable prices and incredible food. They have a great menu of pasta, pizza, etc. I’ve traditionally gone with pizzas, pastas, or sandwiches but went with the calzone today. Incredible and it’s huge, but used quality ingredients.  One of my favorite things about the restaurant is that they have home made Italian cookies for ~$1. They’re always delicious.  I guarantee if you go here you’ll be back very soon.

I'm giving this adorable ristorante a perfect FIVE and I'll be back!  Basically I found this place completely by accident right after working with a new client of mine because I literally smelled a delicious aroma wafting in the lobby of the building where this restaurant is located.  It's a cute Italian family owned business right next to Trump Tower and the owner was sitting at a table when I asked her if the kitchen was still open.  She welcomed me as if it were a kitchen in her own home and even though it was right before closing she never rushed me before, during or after my meal.  I asked her for a recommendation on which personal pizza to try and she suggested the Tartufo which is a thin cut pizza with truffle oil, mozarella, prosciutto, mushrooms and fresh shaved parmegana cheese.  The personal size is generously portioned and I even have half this delicious pizza in my refrigerator because I was unable to finish it all even though the owner insisted I can dine in and take my time. She was so friendly and patient with me and I'm a slow eater. I would love another opportunity to dine here again when I have more time and try one of their desserts too. This restaurant serves homemade, fresh Italian cuisine and it's their family recipe.  You will definitely feel welcomed here and fall in love with their delicious pizzas!

I called and the woman on the phone patiently explained where it is. Very patiently. I walked there with my dog and ran inside to pick up my salad. The male server inside invited me to take a seat outside on the bench with my dog (where my dog was tied) and offered to bring my salad outside. It was such a sweet and kind gesture that I appreciated. Both people went way out of the way to be kind to me. Thank you!  To get there: DO NOT FOLLOW GOOGLE GPS DIRECTIONS! They will take you to Hubbard, below Wabash. The location IS on Wabash in the walkway between the Trump Hotel and Michigan Avenue (the same walkway where Peet's is) but it's not visible from the street, hence the confusion.  If you're looking south down Wabash, you will see a Dunkin Donuts on your right immediately before the Langham and a ton of construction/scaffolding on your left. Immediately before the Trump on your left (again, looking south), you will see a green flag and a walkway that seemingly leads to the river. Go up that walkway and this place will be directly ahead of you on the left. You cannot miss it.

The service was wonderful. We got a 10 inch pepperoni pizza for $6.95, which is a special they have every day.  We also tried a meatball and the stuffed gnocchi in arrabiata  sauce.  The meatball was tender and quite tasty, but nothing amazing.  The tomato sauce it came in tasted like tomato soup.  The arrabiata sauce was very good, but wasn't super spicy.  The gnocchi were pillowy and soft, and had a good amount of riccota and asiago inside.  The pizza was the high point.  The crust was very thin, crisp and had the perfect amount of chew.  There was a good amount of sauce, cheese and pepperoni.  They do not skimp on toppings even with the special.  We sampled the pistachio and spumoni gelato.  It was delicious.  The strawberry gelato in the spumoni tasted more like fresh strawberries than strawberries do.  We will definitely be back for pizza and gelato in the future.
